モブ HK_施設キャラ01-1
モブ HK_施設キャラ01-1
Hey Erika, feeling alright?\n<Guild Master>

Give me a break with the pleasantries. Do I look
alright to you?\n<Erika>
Looks like you've turned the corner. Good, good.\n<Guild Master>
...Was it that bad?\n<Erika>

Your right arm was blown off from the root. The
rest of you is battered inside and out. Anyone
else would've been dead by now.\n<Guild Master>

You've got the vitality of a monster, I'll give
you that.\n<Guild Master>
What about that Minotaur bastard...\n<Erika>
Here.\n<Guild Master>
Ouch, don't throw it. What's this? A ring...?\n<Erika>

It's Ricott's ring. Found it inside its belly.
That's what you were looking for, right?\n<Guild Master>
Ah... So everything's settled then.\n<Erika>

Just cleaning up as we speak. If we leave it,
monsters will come for the carcass.\n<Guild Master>

We're chopping it up and burning it. We're short
on hands. And we still have to dispose of the
thieves' corpses too.\n<Guild Master>
...And what about that little one?\n<Erika>

Issued a bounty for her. She should be reaching
the eastern town by now.\n<Guild Master>
Is that so. Ah-ah...\n<Erika>
You wanted to follow her?\n<Guild Master>

Is that a problem? I'm worried... especially since
she's headed to that kind of town.\n<Erika>

You lost your right arm because of that soft heart
of yours. Wouldn't hurt to reflect on that, would
it?\n<Guild Master>

I was stubborn until I lost my arm. Bending now
would make me look even more foolish.\n<Erika>

...So you're saying you have no intention of
retiring.\n<Guild Master>

I don't know any other way to live... Unless
there's some oddball willing to marry a one-armed
woman.\n<Erika>
That's unlikely.\n<Guild Master>
Don't you have any delicacy at all!?\n<Erika>
Ah, just go away! You have work to do, don't you!?\n<Erika>
I won't heal smelling your old man stink!\n<Erika>
Yeah, I was leaving anyway...\n<Guild Master>
What now?\n<Erika>
You took the medicine I gave you, right?\n<Guild Master>

Tch, you came back just to ask that? You worry too
much.\n<Erika>

Yes, I drank it. Every last drop. Before my arm
got blown off.\n<Erika>

Good. With those injuries, I couldn't have given
it to you now.\n<Guild Master>

It wasn't good at all. It tasted awful. And
despite drinking it, I still got hit once---...\n<Erika>

...Anyway, well, it should be fine probably. They
were all duds anyway.\n<Erika>
...Thanks.\n<Erika>
Yeah.\n<Guild Master>

"Ah, I was planning to take my leave soon without
being told. But before I go, I must give you
this."\n<Guild Master>
"What's up?"\n<Erika>
"It's medicine. You know what's inside, right?"\n<Guild Master>

"It's a strong drug. I couldn't let you drink it
until you woke up."\n<Guild Master>
"..."\n<Erika>

"If you take it 'before that happens,' it will be
effective. Drink it quickly."\n<Guild Master>

"And if 'it' already happened? It's been over a
week, hasn't it?"\n<Erika>
"..."\n<Guild Master>
"...Ah—sorry, sorry. Don't make that face."\n<Erika>

"In the worst-case scenario, I'll have you take
care of it. I know a good doctor."\n<Erika>

"Besides! There's no way those weaklings' pathetic
seeds hit their mark!"\n<Erika>

"...Yes. That is my hope, that is what I'm praying
for."\n<Guild Master>

"Well then, I'm really off to work this time.
Don't walk around too much, okay?"\n<Guild Master>
"Yeah, yeah, get going!"\n<Erika>
"...Haa---...ah...damn it."\n<Erika>
エリカ NI_ST01-1
エリカ NI_ST01-1

"Defeat the bad guys, and everything's resolved,
happily ever after. Everyone lives happily ever
after... like in a fairy tale, huh? It doesn't
work out that way."\n<Erika>

"But well... happiness and sadness at 6:4...
barely a happy ending, I guess I'll settle for
that..."\n<Erika>
"Hey... Serena... thanks..."\n<Erika>
